<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-059-608  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 059 608.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Network  Nov 1989 v3 n6 p15(5).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>What managers really need to know about LANs. (local-areanetworks)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Allan, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The dynamic nature of the local-area-network (LAN) marketplacemakes choosing the right LAN for a given environment difficultwithout a clear understanding of what is currently available.andP;  LANtechnology and implementation issues are described with an eye toenabling managers to use LANs as part of an overall informationprocessing strategy.andP;  Key issues include the need to followstandards such as the IEEE/ANSI802 standard in order to insurefuture flexibility, the need to be prepared for the inevitablegrowth of LANs, the need for a LAN manager and the need to planfor interconnecting other computers and LANs.andP;  Pros and cons ofLANs are listed and LAN concepts and components are detailed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Local Area NetworksSystem SelectionTutorialConnectivity.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Various LAN topologies. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>